<Base title="Support in Shopware 6" description="Support in Shopware 6 – part of your customer impact online. Individual support solutions by Hob by Horse.">
<div class="lp"><section class="hero"><div class="hi">
<p class="kicker">E-Commerce</p>
<h1>Support in Shopware 6 – Part of Your Customer Impact Online</h1>
<p>Support in an online shop remains as important as customer service in a physical store. However, the concerns of your target group change. That is why Hob by Horse develops support solutions tailored to your e-commerce using the Shopware 6 shop system.</p>
</div></section>
<div class="content">
<h2>Setting Up Support in the Online Shop with Developments by Hob by Horse</h2>
<p>Support in e-commerce is the virtual service centre for customer processing. Here questions are answered, customers are guided through the ordering process, complaints are handled and all processes are documented per customer. In Shopware 6, this support is already integrated as part of the sales process.</p>

<h2>Common and Important Online Support Offerings</h2>
<p>In a physical store, support processes are only possible during regular business hours. Online, your target groups expect support availability around the clock and answers to their questions as quickly as possible. For this fast and constant customer service, Hob by Horse develops these strategic support options:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Online contact:</strong> We develop ways to make it as simple as possible for the target group to establish contact with the people responsible for your business support.</li>
<li><strong>Digital service channels:</strong> Classic communication channels are telephone and email. Better is the setup of a live chat that constantly offers communication to customers during their visit to the site. Chatbots for real-time support allow switching between automated communication and real contact with your service staff.</li>
<li><strong>Social networks:</strong> You should be present for your customers on Twitter, Facebook and other social networks. Negative comments or questions appearing there should be answered quickly. This simultaneously strengthens a positive corporate image.</li>
<li><strong>Digital transparency:</strong> Review platforms are rating portals with high acceptance among potential and regular customers. Messaging apps help with shipment tracking without cumbersome support effort.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Industry-Relevant Availability of Online Support</h2>
<p>The support options mentioned are considered standard for support in every online shop of every company size. However, through analysis and market comparison, it is possible to find out which support variant is predominantly used by target groups. Not only the requirements for support, but also the channels used for it differ by industry.</p>

<h2>Achieving Better Customer Satisfaction through Modern Support with Hob by Horse</h2>
<p>Target groups differ in their support expectations according to industries, and also by age, technical experience and gender. Seniors most easily adapt to the operation of your online shop when support offerings are presented in an understandable and easy-to-use way. Younger audiences look for the variant they know from their usual internet behaviour.</p>
<p>Not sure which support in the online shop is appropriate for your target group? Contact Hob by Horse by phone or request more details by email!</p>
</div></div>
</Base>
